ModernNetwork provides HTTPS connectivity for PHP 5.4 on Windows XP.

Modern APIs (OpenAI, Anthropic, Poe, etc.) require TLS 1.2, but PHP 5.2's
SSL libraries only support TLS 1.0. ModernNetwork solves this by using
stunnel as a local TLS tunnel: PHP connects to stunnel on localhost via
plain HTTP, and stunnel handles TLS 1.2 to the remote API.

proxy.php manages stunnel automatically. You do not need to start or
configure stunnel yourself.

Requirements:
- stunnel: https://www.stunnel.org/

Setup:
1. Install stunnel 5.26 on Windows XP.
2. Edit CONF.ini:
   - Set [paths] stunnel to your stunnel.exe path.
   - Set [proxy] port to the local tunnel port (default 8443).
3. Run RUN.cmd. proxy.php will launch stunnel on the first API call.

No separate proxy, hosts-file edit, fixed provider IP, or manual stunnel
startup is part of the supported installation. The generated configuration
sends SNI and verifies the configured API hostname.
